1
00:00:07,001 --> 00:00:11,438
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

2
00:00:11,505 --> 00:00:15,032
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

3
00:00:15,109 --> 00:00:18,545
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

4
00:00:18,612 --> 00:00:22,207
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh! Just go my way</i>

5
00:00:22,283 --> 00:00:25,548
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

6
00:00:25,619 --> 00:00:27,553
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>

7
00:00:29,357 --> 00:00:32,292
<i>Down a difficult road</i>
<i>filled with endless struggles</i>

8
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:36,160
<i>Where do you think you are going</i>
<i>following someone else's map?</i>

9
00:00:36,564 --> 00:00:43,402
<i>An insightful crow comes along</i>
<i>to tear up the map</i>

10
00:00:43,637 --> 00:00:50,702
<i>Now open your eyes and</i>
<i>take a look at the truth (Yeah!)</i>

11
00:00:51,012 --> 00:00:57,144
<i>There's nothing to lose,</i>
<i>so let's GO!!!</i>

12
00:00:57,284 --> 00:01:01,550
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

13
00:01:01,622 --> 00:01:05,217
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

14
00:01:05,292 --> 00:01:08,625
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

15
00:01:08,696 --> 00:01:12,325
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh!</i>
<i>Just go my way</i>

16
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:15,995
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

17
00:01:16,070 --> 00:01:19,562
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best!</i>

18
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:23,235
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

19
00:01:23,310 --> 00:01:27,406
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best! BANG!</i>

20
00:01:47,813 --> 00:01:48,711
Sasuke...

21
00:01:59,925 --> 00:02:01,620
My, my arm!

22
00:02:01,860 --> 00:02:03,521
Are you okay, Lord Orochimaru?

23
00:02:04,129 --> 00:02:05,494
Please take this medicine quickly.

24
00:02:25,083 --> 00:02:26,175
Oh, my...

25
00:02:26,585 --> 00:02:29,281
Just as I get back,
I have to clean the room.

26
00:02:30,288 --> 00:02:32,347
Please make sure you to take
your medicine.

27
00:02:33,325 --> 00:02:36,260
I don't need that kind
of lip service.

28
00:02:37,062 --> 00:02:39,530
It's medicine that I prescribed.

29
00:02:40,065 --> 00:02:42,533
The pain should subside
at least slightly.

30
00:02:43,001 --> 00:02:45,435
The pain on this arm
that seems to burn...

31
00:02:45,937 --> 00:02:49,168
I never thought that it cause
this much suffering.

32
00:02:49,574 --> 00:02:55,171
Sarutobi... known as Third Hokage.
It's his last curse, after all.

33
00:02:55,347 --> 00:02:56,575
Enough of the talking...

34
00:02:57,215 --> 00:02:59,308
More importantly,
has that individual been found?

35
00:02:59,784 --> 00:03:03,481
Yes... She seems to be at a place
called Tanzaku Town.

36
00:03:05,457 --> 00:03:06,856
Tanzaku Town...

37
00:03:10,662 --> 00:03:11,822
Is that so...?

38
00:03:12,664 --> 00:03:16,498
But the opponent is one of the Sannin,
the Legendary Three Ninjas.

39
00:03:17,435 --> 00:03:19,062
It won't be that simple.

40
00:03:22,674 --> 00:03:25,768
Good medicine tends to taste bitter.

41
00:03:37,489 --> 00:03:38,319
Here.

42
00:03:39,658 --> 00:03:43,924
It's the same one...
But this is the trick?

43
00:03:44,396 --> 00:03:47,194
You're the type who was yelled at
at the academy

44
00:03:47,265 --> 00:03:48,493
for not having concentration, right?

45
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:51,094
That doesn't have anything
to do with me now.

46
00:03:52,137 --> 00:03:53,570
Look at this paper.

47
00:03:54,773 --> 00:03:55,569
Uh?

48
00:03:56,541 --> 00:03:57,371
I've seen it.

49
00:03:57,676 --> 00:03:58,540
Fine, then.

50
00:03:58,810 --> 00:04:00,869
Look at it again.

51
00:04:04,950 --> 00:04:05,609
Hmm?

52
00:04:11,856 --> 00:04:12,880
So what is this?

53
00:04:13,458 --> 00:04:17,394
It's not something that
I need to explain in length,

54
00:04:17,462 --> 00:04:19,953
but when you first looked
at this blank piece of paper,

55
00:04:20,031 --> 00:04:22,465
you just glanced at
the whole thing, correct?

56
00:04:23,134 --> 00:04:24,066
Probably.

57
00:04:24,402 --> 00:04:26,836
Then where do you look on this one?

58
00:04:29,307 --> 00:04:31,400
Most likely the point in the middle?

59
00:04:33,011 --> 00:04:36,310
When a human being looks at
just a blank piece of paper,

60
00:04:36,648 --> 00:04:39,981
he doesn't know where to look,
so the eyes wander.

61
00:04:43,855 --> 00:04:46,483
But if you put even a single point on it,

62
00:04:46,725 --> 00:04:48,317
the mind focuses there...

63
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:53,529
This is concentrating at a single point
and as you focus your mind,

64
00:04:53,598 --> 00:04:58,194
you become spiritually stable and
you are able to extract unexpected power.

65
00:04:59,104 --> 00:05:00,264
Huh?

66
00:05:01,273 --> 00:05:04,003
When you opened a hole
on the rubber ball,

67
00:05:04,376 --> 00:05:05,434
you must have been
concentrating desperately

68
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:09,071
to fill up the Chakra
in the palm of your hand.

69
00:05:09,547 --> 00:05:10,479
Yeah, yeah.

70
00:05:11,449 --> 00:05:13,383
When you concentrate,
power emerges.

71
00:05:13,885 --> 00:05:17,878
But without a target,
it is difficult to concentrate.

72
00:05:18,757 --> 00:05:20,122
That's why we have this...

73
00:05:20,425 --> 00:05:22,689
Listen Naruto, from now on,

74
00:05:22,761 --> 00:05:25,423
when you store up the Chakra
you build in your right hand,

75
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:29,191
try to store it up by concentrating
on that mark.

76
00:05:30,268 --> 00:05:31,292
Concentrate...

77
00:05:32,671 --> 00:05:35,469
All right, I'll try it!

78
00:05:36,074 --> 00:05:41,876
<i>Focal Point.</i>
<i>The Mark of the Leaf</i>

79
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:47,848
Concentrate!

80
00:06:00,832 --> 00:06:05,064
Darn it. It's not supposed to be like this.

81
00:06:05,337 --> 00:06:06,770
It has to break like "pang."

82
00:06:13,178 --> 00:06:14,372
Concentrate!

83
00:06:32,030 --> 00:06:34,794
Hello... I'd like to make a little inquiry.

84
00:06:57,222 --> 00:06:58,018
Dang it.

85
00:07:05,864 --> 00:07:07,331
Concentrate.

86
00:07:31,823 --> 00:07:33,814
Concentrate!

87
00:07:41,299 --> 00:07:42,323
No good.

88
00:07:54,012 --> 00:07:58,676
Dang it. What does it mean
to concentrate?!

89
00:08:14,766 --> 00:08:17,792
Damn you, Sarutobi!

90
00:08:41,426 --> 00:08:42,290
All right then...

91
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:45,090
I'm going again to gather
some information.

92
00:08:45,196 --> 00:08:47,664
What...? But you just came.

93
00:08:48,032 --> 00:08:50,227
I don't have any time to waste.

94
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:53,332
Hey, hey...!

95
00:08:53,805 --> 00:08:56,205
Isn't there going to be even
a little soulful game of catch

96
00:08:56,274 --> 00:08:57,832
between the master and pupil?

97
00:08:59,744 --> 00:09:01,644
You scoundrel.

98
00:09:06,851 --> 00:09:08,079
Strike!

99
00:09:09,254 --> 00:09:11,017
Here, the game of catch is over.

100
00:09:13,491 --> 00:09:15,015
See you later.

101
00:09:18,930 --> 00:09:23,958
Humph... I'll forget about that Pervy Sage
and work hard by myself.

102
00:09:27,038 --> 00:09:30,474
<i>That's the only way, Naruto...</i>

103
00:09:30,808 --> 00:09:32,207
<i>You have to do this training alone.</i>

104
00:09:33,111 --> 00:09:35,136
<i>You have the ability to approach</i>
<i>the Fourth Hokage's level...</i>

105
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:37,070
<i>Grasp it by yourself!</i>

106
00:09:41,085 --> 00:09:44,714
Hmm... Never seen her.

107
00:09:45,223 --> 00:09:46,417
If that's the case...

108
00:09:46,858 --> 00:09:48,291
Sorry to bother you.

109
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,785
I know the person.

110
00:09:53,531 --> 00:09:55,897
As well as where she is right now.

111
00:09:56,801 --> 00:09:57,961
I'll buy you a drink.

112
00:09:59,304 --> 00:10:03,502
There's no need.
I was able to win a tidy sum...

113
00:10:03,808 --> 00:10:05,036
Thanks to that lady.

114
00:10:05,443 --> 00:10:08,139
<i>Yeah...you are indeed</i>
<i>the Legendary Sitting Duck.</i>

115
00:10:09,147 --> 00:10:11,911
She lost again, huh.

116
00:10:12,717 --> 00:10:14,810
Her losses started to pile up...

117
00:10:15,053 --> 00:10:16,918
So she was talking about
changing her location.

118
00:10:17,488 --> 00:10:18,420
Where to?

119
00:10:20,391 --> 00:10:25,852
One of the Sannin, Lady Tsunade,
is staying at Tanzaku Town over there.

120
00:10:26,931 --> 00:10:29,263
Then this arm can finally...

121
00:10:29,667 --> 00:10:31,066
Even if it's good medicine,

122
00:10:31,436 --> 00:10:34,428
you won't get away with just
a bitter taste with that person.

123
00:10:34,939 --> 00:10:36,133
It's fine.

124
00:10:43,081 --> 00:10:45,743
Seven, seven, seven...

125
00:10:47,785 --> 00:10:49,946
Seven, seven, seven...

126
00:10:52,223 --> 00:10:55,192
Seven, seven, seven...

127
00:10:56,894 --> 00:10:57,918
Here it comes!

128
00:10:59,897 --> 00:11:01,797
<i>Congratulations to the customer!</i>

129
00:11:01,866 --> 00:11:04,460
<i>Fever has started</i>
<i>on machine number 44.</i>

130
00:11:04,969 --> 00:11:07,665
<i>Now, please keep on getting it out</i>
<i>like a flood.</i>

131
00:11:08,072 --> 00:11:11,303
Lady Tsunade, a rare thing does happen
once in while.

132
00:11:12,744 --> 00:11:14,609
A 37 for me?

133
00:11:19,785 --> 00:11:21,844
Oh wow, lady.

134
00:11:21,987 --> 00:11:24,046
Yeah, what a great work.

135
00:11:24,122 --> 00:11:26,090
Wish I could be favored
by good fortune too.

136
00:11:27,025 --> 00:11:28,890
- Oh, here it comes again!
- Here it comes again!

137
00:11:29,261 --> 00:11:32,025
Yay... it's "fever" again!

138
00:11:36,501 --> 00:11:39,026
<i>A person like me pulls</i>
<i>a big hit like this...</i>

139
00:11:40,606 --> 00:11:42,369
<i>I have a bad premonition.</i>

140
00:11:44,409 --> 00:11:47,901
I also have some knowledge
regarding Lady Tsunade...

141
00:11:48,513 --> 00:11:50,708
I did use to be part of
the Medical Corps, after all.

142
00:11:52,217 --> 00:11:55,744
She was the first person to propose
what is now an accepted practice

143
00:11:55,888 --> 00:12:00,848
of assigning one medical specialist
to a small squad of four.

144
00:12:02,094 --> 00:12:04,119
This was a very revolutionary idea...

145
00:12:04,596 --> 00:12:07,997
A small combat unit that doesn't
even have emergency medical skills,

146
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:12,332
what would happen to them in a battlefield
is clearer than seeing fire.

147
00:12:15,540 --> 00:12:17,770
Countless experiences in war

148
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:21,705
simply became knowledge
to equip themselves with.

149
00:12:22,114 --> 00:12:26,414
Many who were sacrificed
led to the creation of that style.

150
00:12:27,219 --> 00:12:29,847
A person understands the nature
of things for the first time

151
00:12:29,922 --> 00:12:32,686
after losing them.

152
00:12:33,158 --> 00:12:38,357
And the thing created by
one of the legendary Sannin,

153
00:12:39,097 --> 00:12:41,565
who is known as the medical specialist

154
00:12:43,135 --> 00:12:45,194
is that sacrifice.

155
00:12:50,676 --> 00:12:51,700
Not working...

156
00:12:52,611 --> 00:12:55,603
I got to concentrate even more.

157
00:12:58,650 --> 00:13:00,242
<i>Concentrate, concentrate.</i>

158
00:13:01,486 --> 00:13:03,078
<i>Concentrate, concentrate.</i>

159
00:13:03,922 --> 00:13:04,911
<i>Concentrate!</i>

160
00:13:14,466 --> 00:13:15,865
<i>Concentrate...</i>

161
00:13:18,637 --> 00:13:20,832
<i>Concentrate on one point.</i>

162
00:13:29,614 --> 00:13:30,911
<i>Strike!</i>

163
00:13:38,190 --> 00:13:39,521
<i>Strike!</i>

164
00:13:42,694 --> 00:13:45,060
That stupid perve's face floats up
in my head

165
00:13:45,130 --> 00:13:46,961
and I can't even concentrate.

166
00:13:49,401 --> 00:13:51,062
Oh boy...

167
00:13:51,370 --> 00:13:55,238
Some gal somewhere is talking
about me again.

168
00:13:55,474 --> 00:13:57,533
Pinball Games

169
00:13:57,609 --> 00:14:00,077
Wait for me, Lady Tsunade!

170
00:14:00,645 --> 00:14:01,942
What's the matter?

171
00:14:02,014 --> 00:14:05,643
Your winning this much is like a miracle...

172
00:14:05,784 --> 00:14:07,877
But you don't look pleased at all.

173
00:14:09,254 --> 00:14:10,221
This town.

174
00:14:11,089 --> 00:14:11,783
Huh?

175
00:14:11,990 --> 00:14:13,457
I get a bad premonition.

176
00:14:14,226 --> 00:14:15,318
We're going to hurry up and leave.

177
00:14:15,394 --> 00:14:18,329
But this is a tourist resort...

178
00:14:18,397 --> 00:14:20,966
We should take our time and
go see the famous castle and all.

179
00:14:20,966 --> 00:14:23,662
Then we're going to hurry up
and see it so we can leave.

180
00:14:23,902 --> 00:14:25,494
But... Lady Tsunade!

181
00:14:27,973 --> 00:14:28,837
Lord Orochimaru!

182
00:14:29,875 --> 00:14:32,469
Let's get this business over with.

183
00:14:33,245 --> 00:14:36,339
Even if we have to use
a slightly rough method.

184
00:14:43,321 --> 00:14:44,413
I got to do it.

185
00:14:46,691 --> 00:14:47,316
Ouch!

186
00:14:47,926 --> 00:14:52,056
Ouch... It hurts so much,
I can't even build up my Chakra...

187
00:14:53,698 --> 00:14:55,825
<i>He might be reaching his limit soon.</i>

188
00:15:05,977 --> 00:15:09,879
Just a bit... just a bit more rest.

189
00:15:48,687 --> 00:15:49,847
Hey!

190
00:15:50,355 --> 00:15:51,982
You guys, we're in class right now.

191
00:15:53,758 --> 00:15:56,022
You... fools!

192
00:16:00,699 --> 00:16:05,033
You guys have no concentration at all...!

193
00:16:05,403 --> 00:16:08,702
This is not the way to
become fine Ninja.

194
00:16:09,107 --> 00:16:13,703
How can we stay still at a table,
right, Akamaru?

195
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:17,544
I'm hungry.

196
00:16:17,749 --> 00:16:20,274
Sensei, if it's a scolding,
do it quickly.

197
00:16:21,953 --> 00:16:24,387
What the?! You, you guys...

198
00:16:24,990 --> 00:16:26,981
From now, we will have
an after school lesson

199
00:16:27,058 --> 00:16:29,253
to teach you guys more concentration!

200
00:16:29,494 --> 00:16:31,018
- What?!
- What?!

201
00:16:36,168 --> 00:16:37,260
What's this?

202
00:16:38,069 --> 00:16:40,162
You guys are going to do from now

203
00:16:40,238 --> 00:16:42,035
what the predecessors of
the Leaf Village

204
00:16:42,107 --> 00:16:44,371
used to perform every day
as a concentration method!

205
00:16:45,710 --> 00:16:47,337
It is training to build up Chakra

206
00:16:47,412 --> 00:16:51,508
by concentrating your entire energy
on the leaf on your forehead.

207
00:16:51,983 --> 00:16:54,349
It's an ancient way of learning

208
00:16:54,419 --> 00:16:56,387
how not to become distracted
from anything else

209
00:16:56,454 --> 00:16:57,853
by concentrating on a single point,
the leaf.

210
00:16:59,925 --> 00:17:03,326
The one who hones his concentration
is truly a great Ninja...

211
00:17:03,962 --> 00:17:06,897
This is the origin of the Leaf Symbol
on the headband.

212
00:17:07,666 --> 00:17:08,928
That sounds like a lie.

213
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:12,561
Aren't you making that story up
to force us to try harder?

214
00:17:12,704 --> 00:17:15,104
I'm not making this up!
It's a true story.

215
00:17:15,173 --> 00:17:17,641
Anyhow, can you really become
a great Ninja

216
00:17:17,709 --> 00:17:19,176
by just polishing your concentration?

217
00:17:19,244 --> 00:17:22,702
At any rate,
a great Ninja is a guy who's strong.

218
00:17:23,114 --> 00:17:24,342
Hey, you have a point.

219
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:25,709
This stuff...

220
00:17:28,353 --> 00:17:29,843
Bye, bye Sensei!

221
00:17:30,555 --> 00:17:32,546
Hey, hey, you guys wait a minute.

222
00:17:32,624 --> 00:17:34,717
- We won't wait!
- We don't have time for that!

223
00:17:35,293 --> 00:17:38,626
Hey! You misfits!

224
00:17:43,268 --> 00:17:44,860
This is the same thing.

225
00:17:47,405 --> 00:17:51,603
I should have paid more attention
to what Iruka Sensei was saying...

226
00:17:52,944 --> 00:17:54,275
I'm so stupid.

227
00:17:57,649 --> 00:18:01,517
But nothing will start
if I just keep on regretting.

228
00:18:06,258 --> 00:18:10,354
All right, I'm going to master this!

229
00:18:17,068 --> 00:18:19,161
Concentrate, concentrate...

230
00:18:21,039 --> 00:18:22,233
Concentrate!

231
00:18:24,175 --> 00:18:29,374
Wow! Tanzaku Castle sure does have
a commanding presence!

232
00:18:30,115 --> 00:18:33,949
It's worth being designated
as the cultural heritage.

233
00:18:34,286 --> 00:18:36,151
Don't dally...

234
00:18:36,655 --> 00:18:38,350
We're going to hurry up
and leave this town.

235
00:18:39,090 --> 00:18:41,524
Lady Tsunade, please look more carefully...

236
00:18:41,593 --> 00:18:43,527
It costs nothing to view.

237
00:18:48,066 --> 00:18:48,998
Lady Tsunade?

238
00:18:52,370 --> 00:18:54,531
<i>What is this chill?</i>

239
00:19:30,508 --> 00:19:31,202
Now!

240
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:10,011
<i>What a kid...</i>

241
00:20:10,682 --> 00:20:13,708
<i>Raising the density in Chakra</i>
<i>to the point that it burns the palm.</i>

242
00:20:15,153 --> 00:20:17,781
<i>He never ceases to amaze me.</i>

243
00:20:23,695 --> 00:20:24,753
It broke.

244
00:20:25,263 --> 00:20:28,255
Good! The second step seems
to be complete.

245
00:20:28,566 --> 00:20:31,729
Hurry... The third step.

246
00:20:32,103 --> 00:20:33,695
That will come later.

247
00:20:33,805 --> 00:20:35,739
We'll now go meet Tsunade.

248
00:20:48,186 --> 00:20:49,050
That's...

249
00:20:53,691 --> 00:20:54,749
Orochimaru.

250
00:21:02,734 --> 00:21:04,531
I found you.

251
00:21:09,441 --> 00:21:13,377
<i>A cycle of hardship, right?</i>

252
00:21:14,379 --> 00:21:18,338
<i>Inside, we were crying, right?</i>

253
00:21:19,651 --> 00:21:27,615
<i>But the one thing we won't give up</i>
<i>is the dream we've chosen, right?</i>

254
00:21:28,593 --> 00:21:30,686
<i>It's a secondary role,</i>

255
00:21:33,465 --> 00:21:36,491
<i>a role in the shadows</i>

256
00:21:36,935 --> 00:21:41,872
<i>But in reaching for that dream,</i>

257
00:21:42,007 --> 00:21:47,468
<i>let us stay centered,</i>
<i>let us stay true</i>

258
00:21:47,646 --> 00:21:52,549
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we hung on without giving up</i>

259
00:21:52,617 --> 00:21:57,520
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we kept coming back up</i>

260
00:21:57,589 --> 00:22:06,759
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we believed and dreamed</i>

261
00:22:07,232 --> 00:22:12,101
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we've seen fools</i>

262
00:22:12,170 --> 00:22:18,006
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we've stood in the shadows of others</i>

263
00:22:19,644 --> 00:22:29,781
<i>Now, it's our turn...</i>
<i>Let us bask in our dreams</i>

264
00:22:37,462 --> 00:22:41,922
I can master the third step while walking?
Give me a break!

265
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:45,231
Fool! If we don't hurry it up,
we'll lose Tsunade!

266
00:22:45,303 --> 00:22:47,828
Besides, she's short tempered
and impatient!

267
00:22:47,906 --> 00:22:49,174
Where are we heading?

268
00:22:49,174 --> 00:22:52,302
If she's here in this town, we'll just
look for her from somewhere high up.

269
00:22:52,377 --> 00:22:53,969
- So we'll climb up a castle.
- Castle?!

270
00:22:54,045 --> 00:22:56,411
- Can't you see over there?!
- Which way is "over there"?

271
00:22:56,581 --> 00:22:57,479
I'm saying...

272
00:22:57,649 --> 00:23:00,413
Oh! What the?!

273
00:23:01,186 --> 00:23:02,847
Next time: "An Impossible Choice:
The Pain Within Tsunade's Heart"
